1) Find files in directory by pattern names and move to another directory
find . -maxdepth 1 -type f -exec grep -q "pattern" '{}' ';' -exec cp '{}' /path/to/destination ';'

2) Count no of files in a directory
ls | wc -l

3) :%s/\r//g Vim command to remove ^M characters from bash scripts
4) mv `ls | head -500` ./subfolder1/ Move some x files from one dir to a subfolder.

